import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for COST and WMT from Nov 29, 2019
start_date = "2019-11-29"
end_date = "2025-02-28"

print("Fetching data for COST...")
cost_data = yf.download("COST", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for WMT...")
wmt_data = yf.download("WMT", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract the 'Close' column correctly from MultiIndex
cost_prices = cost_data[("Close", "COST")].dropna()
wmt_prices = wmt_data[("Close", "WMT")].dropna()
print("COST Prices Head:\n", cost_prices.head())
print("WMT Prices Head:\n", wmt_prices.head())

# Step 2: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = 0  # Start at initial price
    return initial_price + np.cumsum(random_steps)

cost_rw = random_walk_simulation(cost_prices.iloc[0], len(cost_prices), scale=5)
wmt_rw = random_walk_simulation(wmt_prices.iloc[0], len(wmt_prices), scale=5)

# Step 3: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

cost_returns = cost_prices.pct_change().dropna()
wmt_returns = wmt_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(cost_prices, "COST Prices")
unit_root_test(wmt_prices, "WMT Prices")
unit_root_test(cost_returns, "COST Returns")
unit_root_test(wmt_returns, "WMT Returns")

# Step 4: Fit ARMA Model (ARMA(1,1))
def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

cost_arma = fit_arma(cost_returns, "COST Returns")
wmt_arma = fit_arma(wmt_returns, "WMT Returns")

# Step 5: Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

# Random Walk vs Actual Prices
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(cost_prices.index, cost_prices, label="COST Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(cost_prices.index, cost_rw, label="COST Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(wmt_prices.index, wmt_prices, label="WMT Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(wmt_prices.index, wmt_rw, label="WMT Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price")
plt.legend()

# Returns
plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(cost_returns.index, cost_returns, label="COST Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(wmt_returns.index, wmt_returns, label="WMT Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# ARMA Forecasts (last 30 days)
cost_forecast = cost_arma.forecast(steps=30)
wmt_forecast = wmt_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=cost_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(cost_returns.index[-30:], cost_returns[-30:], label="COST Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, cost_forecast, label="COST ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(wmt_returns.index[-30:], wmt_returns[-30:], label="WMT Actual Returns", color="green")
plt.plot(forecast_index, wmt_forecast, label="WMT ARMA Forecast", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("ARMA(1,1) Forecast vs Actual Returns (Last 30 Days)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Install required libraries in Colab
!pip install yfinance statsmodels matplotlib pandas numpy

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, coint
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for COST and WMT from Nov 29, 2019
start_date = "2019-11-29"
end_date = "2025-02-28"

print("Fetching data for COST...")
cost_data = yf.download("COST", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for WMT...")
wmt_data = yf.download("WMT", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract the 'Close' column
cost_prices = cost_data["Close"].dropna()
wmt_prices = wmt_data["Close"].dropna()
print("COST Prices Head:\n", cost_prices.head())
print("WMT Prices Head:\n", wmt_prices.head())

# Step 2: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = 0  # Start at initial price
    return initial_price + np.cumsum(random_steps)

cost_rw = random_walk_simulation(cost_prices.iloc[0], len(cost_prices), scale=5)
wmt_rw = random_walk_simulation(wmt_prices.iloc[0], len(wmt_prices), scale=5)

# Step 3: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

cost_returns = cost_prices.pct_change().dropna()
wmt_returns = wmt_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(cost_prices, "COST Prices")
unit_root_test(wmt_prices, "WMT Prices")
unit_root_test(cost_returns, "COST Returns")
unit_root_test(wmt_returns, "WMT Returns")

# Step 4: Fit ARMA Model (ARMA(1,1))
def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

cost_arma = fit_arma(cost_returns, "COST Returns")
wmt_arma = fit_arma(wmt_returns, "WMT Returns")

# Step 5: Cointegration Test
def cointegration_test(series1, series2):
    score, p_value, _ = coint(series1, series2)
    print("\nCointegration Test:")
    print(f"t-statistic: {score:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {p_value:.4f}")
    if p_value < 0.05:
        print("The series are cointegrated.")
    else:
        print("The series are not cointegrated.")
    return score, p_value

coint_score, coint_p_value = cointegration_test(cost_prices, wmt_prices)

# Step 6: Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 12))

# Random Walk vs Actual Prices
plt.subplot(4, 1, 1)
plt.plot(cost_prices.index, cost_prices, label="COST Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(cost_prices.index, cost_rw, label="COST Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(wmt_prices.index, wmt_prices, label="WMT Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(wmt_prices.index, wmt_rw, label="WMT Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price")
plt.legend()

# Returns
plt.subplot(4, 1, 2)
plt.plot(cost_returns.index, cost_returns, label="COST Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(wmt_returns.index, wmt_returns, label="WMT Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# ARMA Forecasts (last 30 days)
cost_forecast = cost_arma.forecast(steps=30)
wmt_forecast = wmt_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=cost_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(4, 1, 3)
plt.plot(cost_returns.index[-30:], cost_returns[-30:], label="COST Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, cost_forecast, label="COST ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(wmt_returns.index[-30:], wmt_returns[-30:], label="WMT Actual Returns", color="green")
plt.plot(forecast_index, wmt_forecast, label="WMT ARMA Forecast", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("ARMA(1,1) Forecast vs Actual Returns (Last 30 Days)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# Cointegration Residuals
plt.subplot(4, 1, 4)
residuals = cost_prices - wmt_prices
plt.plot(residuals.index, residuals, label="Cointegration Residuals", color="purple")
plt.title(f"Cointegration Residuals (t-statistic: {coint_score:.4f}, p-value: {coint_p_value:.4f})")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Residuals")
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Install required libraries in Colab
!pip install yfinance statsmodels matplotlib pandas numpy

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, coint
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for COST and WMT from Nov 29, 2019
start_date = "2019-11-29"
end_date = "2025-02-28"

print("Fetching data for COST...")
cost_data = yf.download("COST", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for WMT...")
wmt_data = yf.download("WMT", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract 'Close' prices from MultiIndex
cost_prices = cost_data[("Close", "COST")].dropna()
wmt_prices = wmt_data[("Close", "WMT")].dropna()

# Align indices for cointegration test
combined = pd.concat([cost_prices, wmt_prices], axis=1).dropna()
cost_prices = combined.iloc[:, 0]
wmt_prices = combined.iloc[:, 1]

# Step 2: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = 0
    return initial_price + np.cumsum(random_steps)

cost_rw = random_walk_simulation(cost_prices.iloc[0], len(cost_prices), scale=5)
wmt_rw = random_walk_simulation(wmt_prices.iloc[0], len(wmt_prices), scale=5)

# Step 3: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

cost_returns = cost_prices.pct_change().dropna()
wmt_returns = wmt_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(cost_prices, "COST Prices")
unit_root_test(wmt_prices, "WMT Prices")
unit_root_test(cost_returns, "COST Returns")
unit_root_test(wmt_returns, "WMT Returns")

# Step 4: Fit ARMA Model (ARMA(1,1))
def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

cost_arma = fit_arma(cost_returns, "COST Returns")
wmt_arma = fit_arma(wmt_returns, "WMT Returns")

# Step 5: Correlogram and Partial Correlogram of Residuals
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
plot_acf(cost_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of COST ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
plot_pacf(cost_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of COST ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 3)
plot_acf(wmt_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="ACF of WMT ARMA Residuals")
plt.subplot(2, 2, 4)
plot_pacf(wmt_arma.resid, ax=plt.gca(), title="PACF of WMT ARMA Residuals")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Step 6: Cointegration Test (Engle-Granger)
print("\nCointegration Test (Engle-Granger) between COST and WMT Prices:")
coint_result = coint(cost_prices, wmt_prices)
print(f"Cointegration Test Statistic: {coint_result[0]:.4f}")
print(f"p-value: {coint_result[1]:.4f}")
print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in zip(['1%', '5%', '10%'], coint_result[2])})
if coint_result[1] < 0.05:
    print("Result: Reject the null hypothesis - COST and WMT prices are cointegrated.")
else:
    print("Result: Fail to reject the null hypothesis - COST and WMT prices are not cointegrated.")

# Step 7: Plotting Original Analyses
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

# Random Walk vs Actual Prices
plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(cost_prices.index, cost_prices, label="COST Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(cost_prices.index, cost_rw, label="COST Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(wmt_prices.index, wmt_prices, label="WMT Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(wmt_prices.index, wmt_rw, label="WMT Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price")
plt.legend()

# Returns
plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(cost_returns.index, cost_returns, label="COST Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(wmt_returns.index, wmt_returns, label="WMT Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

# ARMA Forecasts (last 30 days)
cost_forecast = cost_arma.forecast(steps=30)
wmt_forecast = wmt_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=cost_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(cost_returns.index[-30:], cost_returns[-30:], label="COST Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, cost_forecast, label="COST ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(wmt_returns.index[-30:], wmt_returns[-30:], label="WMT Actual Returns", color="green")
plt.plot(forecast_index, wmt_forecast, label="WMT ARMA Forecast", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("ARMA(1,1) Forecast vs Actual Returns (Last 30 Days)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.regression.linear_model import OLS
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for TM (Toyota) and VWAGY (Volkswagen) from Nov 29, 2019
start_date = "2019-11-29"
end_date = "2025-02-28"  # Ajusta a una fecha pasada si falla, ej. "2024-12-31"

print("Fetching data for TM (Toyota)...")
tm_data = yf.download("TM", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for VWAGY (Volkswagen)...")
vwagy_data = yf.download("VWAGY", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract the 'Close' column and align dates
tm_prices = tm_data["Close"].dropna()
vwagy_prices = vwagy_data["Close"].dropna()

# Alinear las series (usar solo fechas comunes)
prices = pd.concat([tm_prices, vwagy_prices], axis=1).dropna()
tm_prices = prices.iloc[:, 0]
vwagy_prices = prices.iloc[:, 1]

print("TM Prices Length:", len(tm_prices))
print("TM Prices Head:\n", tm_prices.head())
print("VWAGY Prices Length:", len(vwagy_prices))
print("VWAGY Prices Head:\n", vwagy_prices.head())

# Step 2: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

unit_root_test(tm_prices, "TM Prices")
unit_root_test(vwagy_prices, "VWAGY Prices")

# Step 3: Cointegration Test (Engle-Granger)
def test_cointegration(series1, series2, name1, name2):
    # Regresión lineal de series1 sobre series2
    model = OLS(series1, pd.DataFrame({'const': 1, name2: series2})).fit()
    residuals = model.resid
    # Prueba ADF sobre los residuos
    result = adfuller(residuals)
    print(f"\nCointegration Test (ADF on residuals) between {name1} and {name2}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] < 0.05:
        print(f"{name1} and {name2} are likely cointegrated.")
    else:
        print(f"No evidence of cointegration between {name1} and {name2}.")

test_cointegration(tm_prices, vwagy_prices, "TM Prices", "VWAGY Prices")

# Step 4: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, index, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = 0  # Start at initial price
    rw_values = initial_price + np.cumsum(random_steps)
    return pd.Series(rw_values, index=index)

tm_rw = random_walk_simulation(tm_prices.iloc[0], len(tm_prices), tm_prices.index, scale=5)
vwagy_rw = random_walk_simulation(vwagy_prices.iloc[0], len(vwagy_prices), vwagy_prices.index, scale=5)

# Step 5: Fit ARMA to Returns (si no están cointegradas)
tm_returns = tm_prices.pct_change().dropna()
vwagy_returns = vwagy_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(tm_returns, "TM Returns")
unit_root_test(vwagy_returns, "VWAGY Returns")

def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

tm_arma = fit_arma(tm_returns, "TM Returns")
vwagy_arma = fit_arma(vwagy_returns, "VWAGY Returns")

# Step 6: Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(tm_prices.index, tm_prices, label="TM Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(tm_rw.index, tm_rw, label="TM Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(vwagy_prices.index, vwagy_prices, label="VWAGY Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(vwagy_rw.index, vwagy_rw, label="VWAGY Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price (USD)")
plt.legend()

plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(tm_returns.index, tm_returns, label="TM Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(vwagy_returns.index, vwagy_returns, label="VWAGY Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

tm_forecast = tm_arma.forecast(steps=30)
vwagy_forecast = vwagy_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=tm_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

# Install required libraries in Colab
!pip install yfinance statsmodels matplotlib pandas numpy

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import yfinance as yf
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.regression.linear_model import OLS
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

# Set random seed for reproducibility
np.random.seed(42)

# Step 1: Fetch stock data for VZ (Verizon) and TMUS (T-Mobile) from Nov 29, 2019
start_date = "2019-11-29"
end_date = "2025-02-28"  # Hasta el último día disponible antes de hoy

print("Fetching data for VZ (Verizon)...")
vz_data = yf.download("VZ", start=start_date, end=end_date)
print("Fetching data for TMUS (T-Mobile)...")
tmus_data = yf.download("TMUS", start=start_date, end=end_date)

# Extract the 'Close' column and align dates
vz_prices = vz_data["Close"].dropna()
tmus_prices = tmus_data["Close"].dropna()

# Alinear las series (usar solo fechas comunes)
prices = pd.concat([vz_prices, tmus_prices], axis=1).dropna()
vz_prices = prices.iloc[:, 0]
tmus_prices = prices.iloc[:, 1]

print("VZ Prices Length:", len(vz_prices))
print("VZ Prices Head:\n", vz_prices.head())
print("TMUS Prices Length:", len(tmus_prices))
print("TMUS Prices Head:\n", tmus_prices.head())

# Step 2: Unit Root Test (ADF)
def unit_root_test(series, name):
    result = adfuller(series.dropna())
    print(f"\nUnit Root Test (ADF) for {name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] > 0.05:
        print(f"{name} likely has a unit root (non-stationary).")
    else:
        print(f"{name} does not have a unit root (stationary).")

unit_root_test(vz_prices, "VZ Prices")
unit_root_test(tmus_prices, "TMUS Prices")

# Step 3: Cointegration Test (Engle-Granger)
def test_cointegration(series1, series2, name1, name2):
    model = OLS(series1, pd.DataFrame({'const': 1, name2: series2})).fit()
    residuals = model.resid
    result = adfuller(residuals)
    print(f"\nCointegration Test (ADF on residuals) between {name1} and {name2}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic: {result[0]:.4f}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]:.4f}")
    print("Critical Values:", {k: round(v, 4) for k, v in result[4].items()})
    if result[1] < 0.05:
        print(f"{name1} and {name2} are likely cointegrated.")
    else:
        print(f"No evidence of cointegration between {name1} and {name2}.")

test_cointegration(vz_prices, tmus_prices, "VZ Prices", "TMUS Prices")

# Step 4: Simulate a Random Walk
def random_walk_simulation(initial_price, steps, index, scale=1):
    random_steps = np.random.normal(loc=0, scale=scale, size=steps)
    random_steps[0] = 0  # Start at initial price
    rw_values = initial_price + np.cumsum(random_steps)
    return pd.Series(rw_values, index=index)

vz_rw = random_walk_simulation(vz_prices.iloc[0], len(vz_prices), vz_prices.index, scale=5)
tmus_rw = random_walk_simulation(tmus_prices.iloc[0], len(tmus_prices), tmus_prices.index, scale=5)

# Step 5: Fit ARMA to Returns
vz_returns = vz_prices.pct_change().dropna()
tmus_returns = tmus_prices.pct_change().dropna()

unit_root_test(vz_returns, "VZ Returns")
unit_root_test(tmus_returns, "TMUS Returns")

def fit_arma(series, name):
    model = ARIMA(series, order=(1, 0, 1))
    fit = model.fit()
    print(f"\nARMA(1,1) Model Summary for {name}:")
    print(fit.summary().tables[1])
    return fit

vz_arma = fit_arma(vz_returns, "VZ Returns")
tmus_arma = fit_arma(tmus_returns, "TMUS Returns")

# Step 6: Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 10))

plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
plt.plot(vz_prices.index, vz_prices, label="VZ Actual", color="blue")
plt.plot(vz_rw.index, vz_rw, label="VZ Random Walk", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(tmus_prices.index, tmus_prices, label="TMUS Actual", color="green")
plt.plot(tmus_rw.index, tmus_rw, label="TMUS Random Walk", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("Stock Prices vs Random Walk Simulation (Verizon vs T-Mobile)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Price (USD)")
plt.legend()

plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
plt.plot(vz_returns.index, vz_returns, label="VZ Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(tmus_returns.index, tmus_returns, label="TMUS Returns", color="green")
plt.title("Daily Returns (Verizon vs T-Mobile)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

vz_forecast = vz_arma.forecast(steps=30)
tmus_forecast = tmus_arma.forecast(steps=30)
forecast_index = pd.date_range(start=vz_returns.index[-1], periods=30, freq="B")

plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
plt.plot(vz_returns.index[-30:], vz_returns[-30:], label="VZ Actual Returns", color="blue")
plt.plot(forecast_index, vz_forecast, label="VZ ARMA Forecast", color="orange", linestyle="--")
plt.plot(tmus_returns.index[-30:], tmus_returns[-30:], label="TMUS Actual Returns", color="green")
plt.plot(forecast_index, tmus_forecast, label="TMUS ARMA Forecast", color="red", linestyle="--")
plt.title("ARMA(1,1) Forecast vs Actual Returns (Last 30 Days)")
plt.xlabel("Date")
plt.ylabel("Returns")
plt.legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
